flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Scheduled release window or detected need for software update.]
  A --> N1[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Plan and schedule global OTA software deployment campaigns.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Remote Functions - Validate SOTA packages on test fleets and environments.]
  N2 --> N3[PB: Process Builder - Execute phased OTA deployments.]
  N3 --> N4[PB: UI Screens - Monitor deployment progress and success rates.]
  N4 --> N5[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Forecast and plan for required server capacity.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Remote Functions - Maintain accurate records of software versions deployed.]
  N6 --> N7{Decision: Scheduling global OTA software deployment campaigns, determining validation scope, phased deployment strategy, rollback/remediation actions, infrastructure capacity, and post-deployment version tracking.}
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced working capital tied to failed deployments, minimized COGS through optimized capacity, improved OTIF, and enhanced revenue protection.]
  N7 -->|Deployment failure detected.| B1[Initiate rollback and remediation actions.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Minimize customer impact and engineering effort.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N7 -->|Insufficient server capacity forecasted.| B2[Adjust deployment schedule or allocate additional resources.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Prevent outages and ensure successful deployments.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N7 -->|Inconsistent software version tracking.| B3[Update version tracking records.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Maintain accurate fleet software inventory.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]